{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T16:56:14.030Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_07acb54591783f13016a5d01ac55608191afeb2662cb29ea7c","status":"completed","call_id":"call_a3LieUIYZqZ3JslHQw2kwxYa","name":"exec","input":"const r = await tools.exec_command({\n  cmd: \"rg -n -C 8 \\\"local.*gate|Before.*push|test:e2e:integration|image:security|infra:check|test:integration:postgres|test:unit:server|test:unit:app|format:check\\\" README.md QUALITY.md package.json .github/workflows/pr-quality.yml .github/workflows/e2e-baseline.yml | sed -n '1,420p'\",\n  workdir: \"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/b7e9/evorto\",\n  yield_time_ms: 10000,\n  max_output_tokens: 40000\n});\ntext(r.output);\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f7b3b-61db-7f22-b04f-a7cc62c9b8f9"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T16:56:14.134Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","id":"ctco_019f7b4e-9036-7d40-bd59-9ab3617fee66","call_id":"call_a3LieUIYZqZ3JslHQw2kwxYa","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.1 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"README.md-89-To build the project run:\nREADME.md-90-\nREADME.md-91-```bash\nREADME.md-92-bun run build:app\nREADME.md-93-```\nREADME.md-94-\nREADME.md-95-This will compile your project and store the build artifacts in the `dist/` directory. By default, the production build optimizes your application for performance and speed.\nREADME.md-96-\nREADME.md:97:## Mandatory local CI gate\nREADME.md-98-\nREADME.md:99:Before any push, PR update, or other action that can trigger CI, the exact local\nREADME.md-100-equivalent of every triggered CI suite must pass completely. Run the canonical,\nREADME.md-101-unfiltered commands below against the commit that will be pushed:\nREADME.md-102-\nREADME.md-103-```bash\nREADME.md-104-bun install --frozen-lockfile\nREADME.md-105-bun run release:validate\nREADME.md-106-bun run format:write\nREADME.md:107:bun run format:check\nREADME.md-108-bun run lint\nREADME.md-109-git diff --exit-code\nREADME.md-110-test -z \"$(git status --porcelain=v1)\"\nREADME.md:111:bun run test:unit:server\nREADME.md-112-bun run test:unit\nREADME.md:113:bun run test:integration:postgres:local\nREADME.md-114-bun run build:app\nREADME.md:115:bun run infra:check\nREADME.md:116:bun run image:security:local\nREADME.md-117-bun run test:e2e\nREADME.md-118-bun run test:e2e:docs\nREADME.md-119-```\nREADME.md-120-\nREADME.md-121-Every collected test must pass with zero skips, todos, fixmes, expected\nREADME.md-122-failures, retries/flakes, interruptions, or focused tests. Missing services,\nREADME.md:123:credentials, environment variables, or local tools block the gate; they are not\nREADME.md-124-reasons to defer a suite to CI. Commands with forwarded file, filter, project,\nREADME.md-125-shard, `--changed`, or reporter arguments are useful diagnostics but never\nREADME.md-126-satisfy the final gate. See [QUALITY.md](QUALITY.md) for the done criteria and\nREADME.md-127-[tests/README.md](tests/README.md) for the disposable PostgreSQL prerequisite.\nREADME.md-128-The infrastructure commands validate and scan both Terraform roots, then build,\nREADME.md-129-inspect, inventory, and vulnerability-scan the real Linux/amd64 runtime image.\nREADME.md-130-\nREADME.md-131-The block above is the normal pull-request baseline. Any caller-forwarded\nREADME.md-132-selector beyond a canonical package script that reduces collection is\nREADME.md-133-diagnostic-only, including file arguments, `--filter`, `--grep`,\nREADME.md-134-`--grep-invert`, `--include`, `--last-failed`, `--related`, project, shard,\nREADME.md:135:`--changed`, or reporter overrides. Before any push, PR update, merge, or\nREADME.md:136:release that triggers provider certification, the local provider gate requires\nREADME.md-137-both commands, in this order:\nREADME.md-138-\nREADME.md-139-```bash\nREADME.md:140:bun run test:e2e:integration\nREADME.md-141-bun run test:e2e:live-esncard:release\nREADME.md-142-```\nREADME.md-143-\nREADME.md-144-The integration command requires the approved Auth0 Management and Google Maps\nREADME.md-145-credentials. The second command requires both protected ESNcard provider\nREADME.md-146-identifiers—one active and one permanently expired—and certifies only the\nREADME.md-147-ESNcard provider portion. Both runs must pass entirely with the same\nREADME.md-148-zero-failure, zero-skip, zero-todo, zero-fixme,\n--\npackage.json-7-    \"dev:start\": \"bun run env:runtime && dotenv -c dev -- sh -c 'bun run dev:ng serve --port \\\"$APP_HOST_PORT\\\"'\",\npackage.json-8-    \"build:app\": \"NG_BUILD_PARTIAL_SSR=1 bun run dev:ng build && bun run build:ops\",\npackage.json-9-    \"build:ops\": \"bun run build:ops:schema && bun run build:ops:prerequisites && bun run build:ops:reset && bun run build:ops:seed\",\npackage.json-10-    \"build:ops:prerequisites\": \"bun build src/server/ops/database-prerequisites.ts --target=bun --minify --outfile dist/evorto/ops/database-prerequisites.mjs\",\npackage.json-11-    \"build:ops:schema\": \"bun build src/db/schema/index.ts --target=bun --packages=external --minify --outfile dist/evorto/ops/schema.mjs\",\npackage.json-12-    \"build:ops:reset\": \"bun build src/server/ops/reset-staging-database.ts --target=bun --minify --outfile dist/evorto/ops/reset-staging-database.mjs\",\npackage.json-13-    \"build:ops:seed\": \"bun build helpers/database.ts --target=bun --minify --outfile dist/evorto/ops/seed-staging.mjs\",\npackage.json-14-    \"image:verify\": \"bash ops/scaleway/verify-runtime-image.sh\",\npackage.json:15:    \"image:security:local\": \"bun run env:runtime && dotenv -c dev -- bash ops/scaleway/verify-image-security.sh\",\npackage.json:16:    \"infra:check\": \"bash ops/scaleway/verify-terraform.sh\",\npackage.json-17-    \"build:watch\": \"NG_BUILD_PARTIAL_SSR=1 bun run dev:ng build --watch --configuration development\",\npackage.json-18-    \"test:unit\": \"bun run dev:ng test\",\npackage.json:19:    \"test:unit:server\": \"bunx vitest run --config vitest.config.ts\",\npackage.json-20-    \"release:validate\": \"bash helpers/testing/validate-knope.sh\",\npackage.json:21:    \"test:integration:postgres\": \"bun helpers/testing/run-postgres-integration.ts\",\npackage.json:22:    \"test:integration:postgres:local\": \"POSTGRES_INTEGRATION_DISPOSABLE=true dotenv -c dev -- bun helpers/testing/run-postgres-integration.ts\",\npackage.json-23-    \"lint\": \"bun run dev:ng lint --fix\",\npackage.json:24:    \"format:check\": \"prettier --check .\",\npackage.json-25-    \"format:write\": \"prettier --write .\",\npackage.json-26-    \"test:e2e:check\": \"bun run env:runtime && dotenv -c dev -- bun helpers/testing/runtime-preflight.ts playwright\",\npackage.json-27-    \"test:e2e\": \"bun run test:e2e:check && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test --project=local-chrome-baseline\",\npackage.json-28-    \"test:e2e:ui\": \"bun run test:e2e:check && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test --project=setup --trace=off && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images PLAYWRIGHT_SAFE_UI_BASELINE=1 dotenv -c dev -- playwright test --ui\",\npackage.json:29:    \"test:e2e:integration\": \"bun run test:e2e:check && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test --project=local-chrome-integration --project=docs-integration\",\npackage.json-30-    \"test:e2e:live-esncard\": \"bun run env:runtime && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- bun helpers/testing/runtime-preflight.ts esncard-release && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test tests/specs/profile/user-profile-live-esncard.spec.ts tests/docs/profile/discounts.doc.ts --project=local-chrome-live-esncard --project=docs-live-esncard --grep '@needs-live-esncard'\",\npackage.json-31-    \"test:unit:esncard-provider-error\": \"bun run dev:ng test --watch=false --include src/app/profile/user-profile/user-profile.component.spec.ts\",\npackage.json-32-    \"test:e2e:live-esncard:release\": \"bun run env:runtime && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- bun helpers/testing/runtime-preflight.ts esncard-release && bun run test:unit:esncard-provider-error && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test tests/specs/profile/user-profile-live-esncard.spec.ts tests/docs/profile/discounts.doc.ts --project=local-chrome-live-esncard --project=docs-live-esncard --grep '@needs-live-esncard' --trace=off --reporter=./tests/support/reporters/protected-value-sanitizer-reporter.ts,github,dot,./tests/support/reporters/complete-playwright-run-reporter.ts\",\npackage.json-33-    \"test:e2e:docs\": \"bun run test:e2e:check && DOCS_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs DOCS_IMG_OUT_DIR=test-results/docs/images dotenv -c dev -- playwright test --project=docs-baseline\",\npackage.json-34-    \"test:e2e:docs:publish\": \"bun run env:runtime && dotenv -c dev -- bun helpers/testing/publish-documentation.ts\",\npackage.json-35-    \"test:e2e:install\": \"playwright install\",\npackage.json-36-    \"test:e2e:report\": \"playwright show-report\",\npackage.json-37-    \"db:push\": \"bun run env:runtime && dotenv -c dev -- drizzle-kit push --force\",\n--\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-88-              exit 1\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-89-            fi\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-90-            retry_delay_seconds=$((attempt * 15))\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-91-            echo \"::warning::Dependency installation attempt ${attempt} failed; retrying in ${retry_delay_seconds}s\"\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-92-            sleep \"${retry_delay_seconds}\"\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-93-          done\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-94-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-95-      - name: Run PostgreSQL integration tests\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml:96:        run: bun run test:integration:postgres\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-97-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-98-  code-quality:\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-99-    name: Lint, unit tests, and build\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-100-    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-101-    timeout-minutes: 40\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-102-    env:\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-103-      CI: true\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-104-    steps:\n--\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-140-            echo \"::warning::Dependency installation attempt ${attempt} failed; retrying in ${retry_delay_seconds}s\"\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-141-            sleep \"${retry_delay_seconds}\"\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-142-          done\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-143-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-144-      - name: Install Playwright browser for browser-backed security tests\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-145-        run: bunx playwright install --with-deps chromium\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-146-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-147-      - name: Check formatting\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml:148:        run: bun run format:check\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-149-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-150-      - name: Lint without uncommitted fixes\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-151-        run: |\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-152-          bun run lint\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-153-          git diff --exit-code\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-154-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-155-      - name: Run server unit tests\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml:156:        run: bun run test:unit:server\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-157-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-158-      - name: Run application unit tests\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-159-        run: bun run test:unit\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-160-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-161-      - name: Build application\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-162-        run: bun run build:app\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-163-\n.github/workflows/pr-quality.yml-164-  terraform:\n--\nQUALITY.md-224-   and must pass the same fail-closed credential preflight plus the provider\nQUALITY.md-225-   error unit check. A missing identifier fails the run; live-provider coverage\nQUALITY.md-226-   is never converted into a skipped test.\nQUALITY.md-227-\nQUALITY.md-228-## Done Criteria\nQUALITY.md-229-\nQUALITY.md-230-### Local-first CI gate\nQUALITY.md-231-\nQUALITY.md:232:Before any push, PR update, or other action that can trigger CI, run the full\nQUALITY.md-233-local equivalent of every CI test suite that the change will trigger. The local\nQUALITY.md-234-run must complete entirely: every collected test passes, with zero failures,\nQUALITY.md-235-skips, todos, fixmes, expected failures, retries/flakes, interrupted tests, or\nQUALITY.md-236-focused tests. A suite that omits tests because a database, external service,\nQUALITY.md-237-environment variable, or credential is unavailable does not satisfy this gate.\nQUALITY.md-238-Resolve the dependency and rerun locally before CI is attempted. CI is\nQUALITY.md-239-confirmation of an already-green local result, not the first place to discover\nQUALITY.md-240-whether the complete suite passes.\n--\nQUALITY.md-243-enforce completeness within each collected suite at runtime: skipped, todo,\nQUALITY.md-244-interrupted, expected-failure, retried/flaky, or focused tests make the run\nQUALITY.md-245-fail. Any caller-forwarded selector beyond a canonical package script that\nQUALITY.md-246-reduces collection is diagnostic-only and never counts as final gate evidence,\nQUALITY.md-247-including file arguments, `--filter`, `--grep`, `--grep-invert`, `--include`,\nQUALITY.md-248-`--last-failed`, `--related`, project, shard, `--changed`, or reporter\nQUALITY.md-249-overrides. Run the complete PR-equivalent command set documented in `README.md`;\nQUALITY.md-250-one selected suite or a clean source scan never replaces the complete runtime\nQUALITY.md:251:result. Before any push, PR update, merge, or release that triggers provider\nQUALITY.md:252:certification, run both `bun run test:e2e:integration` with the approved Auth0\nQUALITY.md-253-Management and Google Maps credentials and\nQUALITY.md-254-`bun run test:e2e:live-esncard:release` with the protected live-provider\nQUALITY.md-255-active and permanently expired identifiers. The live ESNcard provider portion\nQUALITY.md-256-is not the whole provider gate. Both commands must finish locally with\nQUALITY.md-257-every collected test passing and zero incomplete outcomes before CI is\nQUALITY.md-258-attempted. Cloudflare Images is being removed and is not a release gate.\nQUALITY.md-259-\nQUALITY.md-260-Stripe tax-rate metadata has non-null account ownership in the fresh target\n--\nQUALITY.md-281-`/readyz` proves behavior, not commit identity. `docker:resume` is valid only\nQUALITY.md-282-for an already initialized plain PostgreSQL/MinIO/Mailpit/Stripe/web/worker\nQUALITY.md-283-Compose project whose one-shot database and bucket setup completed\nQUALITY.md-284-successfully. Use `docker:start` for an intentional schema reset and reseed;\nQUALITY.md-285-the disposable Playwright-owned stack removes its project volumes on exit.\nQUALITY.md-286-\nQUALITY.md-287-For a typical change, before finishing:\nQUALITY.md-288-\nQUALITY.md:289:- the local-first CI gate passes for every CI suite the change will trigger\nQUALITY.md-290-- lint/format expectations are satisfied\nQUALITY.md-291-- new or changed behavior has tests where practical\nQUALITY.md-292-- Browser walkthrough was performed for UI behavior changes\nQUALITY.md-293-- Playwright coverage was added or updated for durable behavior\nQUALITY.md-294-- generated docs were updated for relevant user/admin workflow changes\nQUALITY.md-295-- screenshots are provided for visual changes\nQUALITY.md-296-- the feature has a discoverable click path\nQUALITY.md-297-- release/change-file expectations are met when release-relevant\n"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f7b3b-61db-7f22-b04f-a7cc62c9b8f9"}}}
